    "what_description": "Endostemon viscosus is a species of flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae. It is an annual herb with a viscid or sticky stem, growing up to 10-30 cm in height, and has a quadrangular to subquadrangular shape. The leaves are opposite, ovate to elliptic in shape, and measure 1-2.5 cm in length, with a cuneate base and a serrated margin. The inflorescence is a spike-like raceme, bearing small, tubular flowers with a corolla length of 3-4 mm and a yellowish-white color. The plant produces four-merous flowers with a calyx of 2-3 mm in length and an upper lip that is notched at the apex.",
