    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Endostemon viscosus improperly include experiencing nausea, which is often caused by excessive consumption of its extracts, leading to stomach irritation. Diarrhea is another potential side effect due to the plant's ability to stimulate gut motility and secretion, resulting in increased bowel movements. Developing allergic reactions is also possible, particularly in individuals who are sensitive to certain compounds found in the plant, such as flavonoids and terpenes. Increased heart rate can occur due to the plant's potential to interact with cardiovascular medications and stimulate the sympathetic nervous system, thereby affecting heart function. Furthermore, experiencing diarrhea, which is a common gastrointestinal symptom, may also occur due to the plant's laxative properties.",
